The `partition` function is used to find the index of the pivot value and to swap the elements before and after the pivot. The complexity of the `partition` function is O(n) since it only involves linear search and swapping operations. The `quicksort` function recursively calls the `partition` function until the array is completely sorted. The `quicksort` function takes `low` and `high` as parameters, which are the starting index and the ending index of the array to be sorted. The `partition` function also takes these two parameters as the lower and upper bounds of the range to be sorted.

This C++ implementation of the quicksort algorithm uses the `swap` function to swap two elements. The `swap` function has O(1) time complexity, so the overall time complexity of the `quicksort` function is O(nlog(n)).

